sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2150028
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: In this part, the first promoter pTet is constitutively on, producing T7 RNA polymerase(T7RNAP). T7RNAP can activate the T7 promoter, thus producing the fusion protein in large quantity. The fusion protein(referred to as tetX-GFP) of tetX(a tetracycline-degrading enzyme) and GFP combined with a 3*GGGGS linker is used to report the expression level of tetX.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jianyi Huang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
T7RNAP:PCR amplified from Genome of BL21.
pT7:PCR amplified from BBa_K525998.
As for fusion protein tetX-GFP, tetX is the same as (xxx), the protein linker is provided by our advisor Li Hua, and the GFP is from BBa_E0040. We combine this three parts using overlap extension polymerase chain reaction (OE-PCR).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Two different terminators are used to avoid repeated sequence.
Linker for fusion protein is carefully designed to avoid repeated sequence which may cause problems in assembly.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: p(tetR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence for pTet inverting regulator driven by the TetR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lutz, R., Bujard, H., Nucleic Acids Research (1997) 25, 1203-1210.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_R0040 TetR-Regulated Promoter is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites and the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I2032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Gene 1 coding region from bacteriophage T7 encoding a RNAP polymerase (RNAP). This single-protein RNAP recognizes a 21 bp consensus promoter sequence and is orthogonal to E. coli RNAP.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bartholomew Canton

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong transcriptional terminator consisting of a 20 bp stem-loop that has been engineered to be bidirectional.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG). Subsequently mutations were introduced to make the terminator bi-directional (i.e., AAAAAA insertion on 5' side of the stem loop). Additional mutations were introduced on the 3' side of the stem loop to increase the number of T's and eliminate any promoter -10 site that might be present to avoid initiation of transcription of whatever is downstream.

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pT7
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the T7 promoter without RBS. It has been reported that T7 promoter doesn't work with E.coli RNA polymerase, but only with T7 RNA polymerase(T7RNAP). However, we observed leakage of it in the absence of T7RNAP.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jianyi Huang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We deleted the RBS in BBa_K525998, so that RBS with different efficiency can be used.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: tetX-GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: A fusion protein combining tetX(BBa_K2150101) with GFP(BBa_E0040)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This protein(noted as tetX-GFP) combines a tetracycline-degrading enzyme (tetX monooxygenase, ) with a green fluorescent protein (GFPmt3, BBa_E0040). TetX-GFP has activities of both the tetX and the GFP. As a degradation enzyme, it can degrade tetracycline(tc) and its analogs as we describe (here), and also give the tetracycline resistance to E.coli. As a green fluorescent protein, it inherits the normal function of BBa_E0040. However, the expression quantity of this protein may be smaller than BBa_E0040 under the same promoter or it may take longer time for tetX-GFP to mature, for we notice that when it is expressed under the same promoter as BBa_E0040, the fluorescent intensity(FI) of tetX-GFP is weaker than BBa_E0040 at the same growth stage of E.coli, and it takes longer for E.coli expressing tetX-GFP to reach the same FI as E.coli expressing BBa_E0040. We use tetX-GFP as a monitor of the quantity of tetX expressed in E.coli. TetX-GFP can also act as a reporter of whether our system is working (meaning whether our machine is degrading tetracycline). When tetX-GFP is expressed under a tetracycline-regulated promoter such as BBa_R0040, it will become a visible sensor of tetracycline in the presence of tetR, with no need for additional tetracycline-resistance genes.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yang Ye
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The source of tetX is the same as (xxx), the protein linker is provided by our advisor Li Hua, and the GFP is from BBa_E0040. We combine this three parts using overlap extension polymerase chain reaction (OE-PCR).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The protein linker is 3*GGGGS which provides flexibility to the fusion protein. When choosing the codon for this linker, we need to avoid repeated sequence which may cause problems when assemble these parts.
